    "summary": "Agree, one reservation about poeticality",
    "content": "**Yes, still agree.** One minor reservation:\n\nI would use \"poeticality\" very sparingly, if at all. It sounds like academic jargon and lacks the clean simplicity of \"the poetic.\" Every instance where you might reach for \"poeticality\" can likely be handled by \"the poetic\" or a rephrasing. Reserve it only for contexts where a standard English noun is grammatically unavoidable and \"the poetic\" cannot be made to work.\n\nEverything else -- \"the poetic\" as substantive, \"poetic\" as adjective, capitalized \"the Poetic\" in glossary/introduction -- is exactly right."
